result.name: Supreme Beef Brisket Soup

reviews.text:
We bumped into this small noodle house on our way to Jade market. It’s a hidden gem. The soup of the noodles is so good. It has very tender beef brisket as well as one dried scallop. My son who’s a picky eater loves it. 

The server was rude though. She was showing sour face the entire time and even said very unpleasant words to us about our son. My son wasn’t really screaming or breaking anything. Also, she immediately took a cloth to clean the floor when my son just dropped one tiny piece of noodles on the floor. She, again, was showing face and murmured bad words about my son. 

We quickly finished our food and just left the place. I don’t recommend visiting this place with young kid as long as the woman works there. Two women work there. She is the older one and probably in her 50/60s.

No regrets in coming here. You'll need to eat the beef briskets, either soup or dry version. The beef briskets are so tender and soft, it is just marvelous to savour it. There are also other items on the menu, like curry beef briskets, fish and meat balls, chicken rice and other side dishes. Depending on the time, the shop can be crowded.
Clear soup base. Perfect match with white radish. Seats are really cramped. Not advisable to go in big group.
Do yourself a favour and come eat this beef brisket. A little difficult to find but it’s worth it.
Their beef brisket noodle doesn't dissapoint. The broth is very flavourful and thick. Don't forget to add some dollop of their signature chili oil!
